== 遊戲業界中的女性 ==
據1989年刊於《[[綜藝_(雜誌)|綜藝]]》雜誌上的報導，遊戲業界裡只有3%的女性<ref name=variety2013 />。2013年，[[Lionhead_Studios|Lionhead Studios]]的創意總監Gary Carr預測、未來五至十年內，女性在遊戲業的從業人數將可望提升至50%<ref name=variety2013 />。根據[[Gamasutra|Gamasutra]]在2014所做的遊戲產業從業者薪資調查顯示，從事相同的工作時、美國女性平均比男性少賺14%。其中女性遊戲設計師具有最接近的工資，僅相差4%，女性音效師的工資則和男性相差32%，相差最多。<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/221586/Gender_wage_gap_How_the_game_industry_compares_to_the_US_average.php | first=Kris | last=Graft | title=Gender wage gap: How the game industry compares to the U.S. average | publisher=[[Gamasutra|Gamasutra]] | date=2014-07-22 | accessdate=2015-12-27 | archive-date=2016-01-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160127224543/http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/221586/Gender_wage_gap_How_the_game_industry_compares_to_the_US_average.php | dead-url=no }}</ref>

較知名的女性遊戲從業人員包括[[珍·簡森|珍·簡森]]，《[[狩魔獵人|狩魔獵人]]》的設計師；[[余國荔|余國荔]]，遊戲引擎程式設計師；[[凱莉·聖迪亞戈|凱莉·聖迪亞戈]]，《[[流_(遊戲)|流]]》和《[[花_(遊戲)|花]]》的製作人；[[捷德·雷蒙德|捷德·雷蒙德]]，《[[刺客教條|刺客教條]]》的製作人；[[下村陽子|下村陽子]]，最著名的女電子遊戲作曲家，《[[街頭快打|街頭快打]]》、《[[快打旋風II|快打旋風II]]》、《[[王國之心|王國之心]]》等暢銷作品的作曲者。

=== 支援團體 ===
Women In Games Special Interest Group 是國際遊戲開發者協會轄下的一個特別小組，力圖促進遊戲業界、工作場所和市場環境中的性別平等。它為遊戲業中的人士提供相關資源和支持，或促進該領域產生更吸引女性入行的動機。此外還會長期統計遊戲業界中的女性從業人口，觀察其消長。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://women.igda.org/about/ |title=About | WIGSIG |publisher=Women.igda.org |date= |accessdate=2015-04-08 |archive-date=2016-07-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160725190646/http://women.igda.org/about/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

Women in Games International成立於2005年，致力於促進全球遊戲業界對女性從業者的包容性。組織的基本信念是促進與電子遊戲開發相關的媒體、教育場所和工作場所能更性別平等且性別友善，進而讓更多的消費者享受到更好的遊戲。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://getwigi.com/ |title=missionstatement |publisher=getwigi.com |date= |accessdate=2016-09-07 |archive-date=2016-09-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160921151453/http://www.getwigi.com/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://getwigi.com|title=WIGI Home|publisher=|accessdate=2017-01-20|archive-date=2017-01-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170111201609/http://www.getwigi.com/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

Women In Games Jobs是一個透過大力支持女性角色典範與提供在遊戲領域工作的女性會感興趣之訊息來促進女性在遊戲中的地位在維持穩固的同時又能提升的組織。該組織於2011年6月2日依據英國{{link-en|2006年公司法|Companies Act 2006}}成立，為非營利性或公眾利益公司。遊戲開發商近年來一直力圖平衡開發團隊與遊戲機使用者的性別比例，有越來越多的女性玩家開始使用 [[Wii|Wii]]和[[任天堂DS|任天堂DS]]。除了增長女性對遊戲業界的興趣以外、更企圖消除女性在傳統的遊戲中所受到的汙名。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.womeningamesjobs.com |title=(WIGJ) for more women in gaming |publisher=Womeningamesjobs.com |date= |accessdate=2015-04-08 |archive-date=2015-04-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150414052943/http://www.womeningamesjobs.com/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 電子遊戲實況裡的女性 ==

女性和遊戲實況的關係一直是坎坷不平的。當YouTube和Twitch推出影片直播服務、且越來越受歡迎後，女性玩家開始投入其中，許多知名的實況主都藉著這次的實況革命而崛起，例如Hafu、 Glitterlanced和Sovitia。遊戲實況主Geneviève Forget在Kotaku的採訪中表示：「在我實況的時候、的確常會有與性相關的騷擾，有些觀眾並不是想看我實況遊戲、也不專注於我的實況，只是在談論我的外表，我只能盡可能地把話題拉回遊戲實況。」<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title = They're Attractive, They're Women, And They Play Games Live On The Internet. But They're Not 'Camwhores.'|url = http://kotaku.com/5982137/theyre-attractive-theyre-women-and-they-play-games-live-on-the-internet-but-theyre-not-camwhores|website = Kotaku|accessdate = 2015-12-08|language = en-US|archive-date = 2015-12-08|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151208143430/http://kotaku.com/5982137/theyre-attractive-theyre-women-and-they-play-games-live-on-the-internet-but-theyre-not-camwhores|dead-url = no}}</ref>

女性遊戲實況主最常受到的批評就是使用像Twitch這樣的平台做為軟調色情網路聊天室的替代品、並在實況中以性暗示行為謀取贊助，而男性玩家的支持便是助長這種行為的主要源頭。29歲的Twitch實況主Vivyan Andrew在[[Kotaku|Kotaku]]的訪問中提到：「沒錯、如果妳是個女人、且妳在進行實況，那這種行為很容易被誤解成妳是在尋求大眾的注意、或/並運用妳的『資產』來尋求贊助，而當實況主的外表所能帶給觀眾的超過實況所產生的樂趣時，誤解很容易便會產生。」<ref name=":0" />

MMOs.com的Terence Chiang撰文表示：「我們的社會文化已經將遊戲視為是男人的愛好了，電腦、科技的領域通常被視為是男性的天下」<ref>{{Cite web|title = Girl Gamers in Streaming and eSports|url = http://mmos.com/editorials/girl-gamers-in-streaming-and-esports|website = MMOs.com|accessdate = 2015-12-08|language = en-US|archive-date = 2015-12-10|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151210190723/http://mmos.com/editorials/girl-gamers-in-streaming-and-esports|dead-url = no}}</ref>。這種根深蒂固的文化會使女性將遊戲當作消遣被視為一件難事。研究發現、有52%的玩家是女性<ref>{{Cite web|title = 52% of gamers are women – but the industry doesn't know it {{!}} Meg Jayanth|url = https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2014/sep/18/52-percent-people-playing-games-women-industry-doesnt-know|website = the Guardian|accessdate = 2015-12-08|archive-date = 2018-02-26|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180226070737/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2014/sep/18/52-percent-people-playing-games-women-industry-doesnt-know|dead-url = no}}</ref>，但由於遊戲是較男性氣質的刻板印象之故，此一現象在主流文化中不甚明顯。

== 性別差異 ==
{{See also|電子遊戲中的性別表徵}}

評論家認為女性對電子遊戲興致缺缺可能和[[電子遊戲中的性別表徵|電子遊戲中的女性形象]]過於負面、及專業和鐵桿玩家表現出來的[[厭女症|厭女態度]]息息相關<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.starcitygames.com/magic/misc/22786_To_My_Someday_Daughter.html|author=Geordie Tait|title=To My Someday Daughter|publisher=Starcitygames.com|accessdate=2015-04-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121117010508/http://www.starcitygames.com/magic/misc/22786_To_My_Someday_Daughter.html|archive-date=2012-11-17|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。在2012年一起遊戲業從業的女性在[[Twitter|Twitter]]上的討論中，[[主題標籤|主題標籤]]''#1reasonwhy''指出，包括過度強調女性角色的性徵、忽略對女性而言重要的議題、職場性騷擾、因性別而異的同工不同酬現象皆是在遊戲業界中常見的性別歧視。<ref>{{cite news|last=Locker|first=Melissa|title=#1ReasonWhy: Women Take to Twitter to Talk about Sexism in Video Game Industry|url=http://newsfeed.time.com/2012/11/27/1reasonwhy-women-take-to-twitter-to-talk-about-sexism-in-video-game-industry/|accessdate=2012-11-29|newspaper=[[TIME_magazine|TIME magazine]]|date=2012-11-27|archive-date=2012-11-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121130002500/http://newsfeed.time.com/2012/11/27/1reasonwhy-women-take-to-twitter-to-talk-about-sexism-in-video-game-industry/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Plunkett|first=Luke|title=Here's a Devastating Account of the Crap Women in the Games Business Have to Deal With. In 2012.|url=http://kotaku.com/5963528/heres-a-devastating-account-of-the-crap-women-in-the-games-business-have-to-deal-with-in-2012|accessdate=2012-11-29|newspaper=[[Kotaku|Kotaku]]|date=2012-11-27|archive-date=2012-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121129142127/http://kotaku.com/5963528/heres-a-devastating-account-of-the-crap-women-in-the-games-business-have-to-deal-with-in-2012|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Hamilton|first=Mary|title=#1reasonwhy: the hashtag that exposed games industry sexism|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/gamesblog/2012/nov/28/games-industry-sexism-on-twitter|accessdate=2012-11-29|newspaper=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|date=2012-11-28|archive-date=2013-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130923185642/http://www.theguardian.com/technology/gamesblog/2012/nov/28/games-industry-sexism-on-twitter|dead-url=no}}</ref>

儘管遊戲性、遊戲技巧或類似的遊戲元素通常是中性的，不過遊戲的表現方式卻與性別有強烈的關係。具體而言、由於遊戲通常被視為是幻想的、逃避現實的，而其中的角色如果與玩家具有相同的性別，則更容易讓玩家帶入，產生同理心與角色認同。<ref name=hex>[[Stephanie_Bendixsen|Bendixsen, Stephanie 'Hex']]. ''[http://www.abc.net.au/technology/articles/2011/02/16/3140624.htm Games 4 Girlz?] {{Wayback|url=http://www.abc.net.au/technology/articles/2011/02/16/3140624.htm |date=20161109111407 }}''. [[Australian_Broadcasting_Corporation|ABC]]. 16 February 2011.</ref> 無論男性玩家或女性玩家都希望遊戲能更寫實，且如果角色的性別更具真實感、則玩家能對投入更多認同<ref name=ng>Ng, Amy. ''[http://www.cnn.com/TECH/computing/9805/25/girls.games.idg What it takes to entice the female gamer] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cnn.com/TECH/computing/9805/25/girls.games.idg |date=20160317030651 }}''. [[CNN|CNN]]. 25 May 1998.</ref>。2009年、一份發布於《{{link-en|新媒體與社會|New Media & Society}}》上的學術研究發現，電子遊戲中有85%的可玩角色是男性<ref name=spark /><ref>{{cite journal |last= Williams|first= Dmitri|last2= Martins|first2= Nicole|last3= Consalvo|first3= Mia|last4= Ivory|first4= James D.|date= 2009|title= The Virtual Census: Representations of Gender, Race and Age in Video Games|journal= [[New_Media_&_Society|New Media & Society]]|publisher= [[Sage_Publications|Sage Publications]]|volume= 11|issue= 5|pages= 815–834|doi= 10.1177/1461444809105354 }}</ref> 。Erin Hamilton認為問題出在將[[女性化|女性化]]和[[女性主義|女性主義]]嵌入一款優秀的電子遊戲中並不容易<ref name=hamilton>Hamilton, Erin. "[https://web.archive.org/web/20090211101758/http://www.gamespot.com/gamespot/features/all/gamespotting/102702/8.html The Girl Gamer's Manifesto]". GameSpot. 2008.</ref>，當女性角色出現在電子遊戲中時，無論男性或女性玩家都認為她們在視覺上傳遞出不切實際的身體形象、還有不健康的、刺激性慾的和暴力的訊息<ref>O'Brien, Lucy. ''[http://www.stuff.co.nz/technology/games/2396496/Confessions-of-a-girl-gamer Confessions of a girl gamer] {{Wayback|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/technology/games/2396496/Confessions-of-a-girl-gamer |date=20150924170935 }}''. [[Stuff.co.nz|Stuff.co.nz]]. 9 May 2009.</ref> 。刻板陳舊的、且通常並不帶有諷刺涵義的女性角色表現──例如咯咯咯地傻笑或是愣在那兒什麼都不幹──會導致小孩（特別是認同該女性角色的女孩）認為這是女孩子該有的言行舉止<ref name=reuters>''[https://web.archive.org/web/20030805000714/http://abcnews.go.com/sections/tech/DailyNews/videogamestudy001214.html Not a Pretty Picture]''. [[Reuters|Reuters]] (via [[ABC_News|ABC News]]). 2000.</ref>。此外、讓[[蘿拉·卡芙特|蘿拉·卡芙特]]之類<ref name=hamilton /> 衣著暴露的女性角色在電子遊戲裡賣弄性感<ref name=ng /><ref name=spark />是不會受到部份女性歡迎的。<ref name=kelly>Kelly, Kevin. ''[http://www.joystiq.com/2007/03/21/sxsw-getting-girls-into-the-game-designing-and-marketing-games SXSW: Getting Girls Into The Game: Designing and Marketing Games for Female Players] {{Wayback|url=http://www.joystiq.com/2007/03/21/sxsw-getting-girls-into-the-game-designing-and-marketing-games |date=20150128192759 }}''. [[Joystiq|Joystiq]]. 21 March 2007.</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Behm-Morawitz|first=Elizabeth|title=The Effects of the Sexualization of Female VideoGame Characters on Gender Stereotypingand Female Self-Concept|url=http://www.academia.edu/1865189/The_Effects_of_the_Sexualization_of_Female_Video_Game_Characters_on_Gender_Stereotyping_and_Female_Self-Concept|publisher=Department of Communication, University of Missouri-Columbia|accessdate=2014-04-21|archive-date=2014-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140927065450/http://www.academia.edu/1865189/The_Effects_of_the_Sexualization_of_Female_Video_Game_Characters_on_Gender_Stereotyping_and_Female_Self-Concept|dead-url=no}}</ref>

縱使遊戲角色過度[[性化|性化]]、而一些男性玩家也已成為[[電子遊戲中的性別歧視主義|電子遊戲中對女性玩家的騷擾]]源頭<ref>{{cite web|last=Wallace|first=Amanda|title=Your Argument is Invalid: Harassment Against Female Gamers|url=http://www.gameskinny.com/b0zks/your-argument-is-invalid-harassment-against-female-gamers|publisher=Game Skinny|accessdate=2014-05-05|archive-date=2014-05-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140507083328/http://www.gameskinny.com/b0zks/your-argument-is-invalid-harassment-against-female-gamers|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但遊戲業界裡的男性從業人員也認同遊戲中的女性過度性化的問題<ref>{{cite web|last=Meixsell|first=Jesse|title=Female sexualization in gaming: a male gamer's perspective|url=http://venturebeat.com/2014/04/14/female-sexualization-in-gaming-a-male-gamers-perspective/|publisher=Games Beat|accessdate=2014-05-05|archive-date=2014-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505220315/http://venturebeat.com/2014/04/14/female-sexualization-in-gaming-a-male-gamers-perspective/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。還有部份男性玩家認為，電子遊戲中對女性角色的性化也同樣適用於男性，而如果在合適的情境下、這些於電子遊戲中對男性或女性在性上的描寫是可以被接受的。<ref>{{cite web|last=Pleasure|first=Crymson Pleasure|title=He said what? A male perspective on females in gaming|url=http://realwomenofgaming.wordpress.com/2014/04/04/he-said-what-a-male-perspective-on-females-in-gaming/|publisher=Real Women of Gaming|accessdate=2014-05-05|archive-date=2014-05-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140505222546/http://realwomenofgaming.wordpress.com/2014/04/04/he-said-what-a-male-perspective-on-females-in-gaming/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 影響 ===
[[視電子遊戲為藝術|將電子遊戲視為一種藝術形式]]的概念是在2000年後半興起的，美國{{link-en|國家藝術基金會|National Endowment for the Arts}}在2011年5月認定遊戲是一種藝術形式<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.escapistmagazine.com/news/view/109835-Games-Now-Legally-Considered-an-Art-Form-in-the-USA | title = Games Now Legally Considered an Art Form (in the USA) | first = John | last = Funk | date = 2011-05-06 | accessdate = 2011-05-06 | publisher = [[The_Escapist_(magazine)|Escapist]] | archive-date = 2011-05-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110509072304/http://www.escapistmagazine.com/news/view/109835-Games-Now-Legally-Considered-an-Art-Form-in-the-USA | dead-url = yes }}</ref>。舉例而言、在將電子遊戲視為文化產品並將電玩產業視為文化產業的觀點中，女性在業界裡的聲量和受遊戲啟發後參與文化對話的管道在這個媒體裡都是受到剝奪的<ref name=spark>Young, Nora & Misener, Dan. ''[http://www.cbc.ca/spark/full-interviews/2010/11/02/full-interview-jennifer-jenson-on-girls-gaming/ Repeat of Spark 126 – October 16 & 19, 2011: Games and Girls] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cbc.ca/spark/full-interviews/2010/11/02/full-interview-jennifer-jenson-on-girls-gaming/ |date=20141006075029 }}'' (Podcast available: [http://podcast.cbc.ca/spark/plus-spark_20101102_jenjensonfull.mp3 Full Interview: Jennifer Jenson on Girls & Gaming] {{Wayback|url=http://podcast.cbc.ca/spark/plus-spark_20101102_jenjensonfull.mp3 |date=20101103014859 }}). ''[[Spark_(radio_show)|Spark]]''. 7 November 2010.</ref>。從教育的角度看來，某些[[電子遊戲類型|遊戲類型]]特別缺乏女性的玩家──例如[[第一人稱射擊遊戲|第一人稱射擊遊戲]]有助於提升空間掌握的能力──會使得不同性別者在能力的差異更加明顯<ref name=spark />。而遊玩電子遊戲也為兒童提供了接觸和學習電腦或電子器材的機會，進而使男性在電子遊戲和電腦科學的領域獲得更進一步發展<ref name=nzegwu>Nzegwu, Uzoamaka. ''[http://fubini.swarthmore.edu/~WS30/WS30F2000/compvideo.html Gender and Computer/Video games] {{Wayback|url=http://fubini.swarthmore.edu/~WS30/WS30F2000/compvideo.html |date=20160304071632 }}''. [[Swarthmore_College|Swarthmore]]. 15 May 2000.</ref>。隨著科學技術和網際網路在21世紀後日趨重要，女性在電子遊戲領域的缺席可能會導致女性喪失了部份的相關工作機會。<ref name=spark />

=== 應對 ===
在遊戲開發團隊裡的從業人員多數是男性<ref>{{cite web|last=Burrows|first=Leah|title=Women remain outsiders in video game industry|url=http://www.bostonglobe.com/business/2013/01/27/women-remain-outsiders-video-game-industry/275JKqy3rFylT7TxgPmO3K/story.html|work=The Boston Globe|publisher=Globe Correspondent|accessdate=2014-04-15|archive-date=2014-04-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416173744/http://www.bostonglobe.com/business/2013/01/27/women-remain-outsiders-video-game-industry/275JKqy3rFylT7TxgPmO3K/story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，研究人員發現、增加女性玩家的有效方法之一便是讓作者的身份成為誘因，例如為了回應支持者要求而將《[[哈利·波特|哈利·波特]]》系列遊戲裡的[[妙麗·格蘭傑|妙麗·格蘭傑]]設計為可玩角色<ref name=dillon>Dillon, Beth A. ''[http://www.gamasutra.com/view/feature/2694/event_wrapup_girls_n_games_2006.php Event Wrap-Up: Girls 'N Games 2006] {{Wayback|url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/feature/2694/event_wrapup_girls_n_games_2006.php |date=20161226035200 }}''. [[Gamasutra|Gamasutra]]. 18 May 2006.</ref>。而解決女性玩家在文化上的刻板印象問題的方法之一是直接干涉業界，例如安排女性進入這個行業<ref name=spark />：諸如WomenGamers.com和Sony's G.I.R.L.等組織試圖向女性玩家提供獎學金驅使她們進入遊戲開發業<ref>Caron, Frank. ''[http://arstechnica.com/gaming/news/2007/02/7225.ars Girl gamer scholarship hopes to interest females in games industry] {{Wayback|url=http://arstechnica.com/gaming/news/2007/02/7225.ars |date=20110910194739 }}''. [[Ars_Technica|Ars Technica]]. 2008.</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=SONY ONLINE ENTERTAINMENT NOW ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS FOR THE 2014 G.I.R.L. SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAM|url=https://www.soe.com/girl/|work=soe|publisher=Sony|accessdate=2014-04-21|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140421082811/https://www.soe.com/girl/|archivedate=2014-04-21}}</ref>遊戲開發商如Check Six Games、Her Interactive、Silicon Sisters和Purple Moon都曾公開徵求女性遊戲設計師與遊戲程式設計師。<ref name=yap>Yap, Tammy. ''[https://web.archive.org/web/20031004195707/http://alumweb.mit.edu/whatmatters/200112.shtml What's So Great About Computer Games?]''. [[Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology|MIT]]. 2002.</ref><ref name=nzegwu />

面對產業的未來，許多研究人員認為遊戲業應該要改採性別中立的作法，而另一部份的人則呼籲應該特別針對女性。<ref name=hex /><ref name=hamilton /><ref>{{cite news|author=Rosen, Jill|title=The gender divide: video-gaming has been largely a man's- or boy's- world, but with games by and for women, that's starting to change|work=[[The_Baltimore_Sun|The Baltimore Sun]]|date=September 2008|location=Maryland|page=C1|type=Print}}</ref>最早嘗試將市場拓展到女性方面的例子之一是[[Sega|Sega]]<ref name=hamilton />，該企業旗下的格鬥遊戲中出現越來越多的女性角色<ref name=nzegwu />。其它的例子包括《[[質量效應3|質量效應3]]》、《[[記憶駭客|記憶駭客]]》、《[[最後生還者|最後生還者]]》等可讓玩家選擇女性作為主角的遊戲。<ref name="Dewitt">{{cite web|last=Dewitt|first=James|title=Lara Croft and the Future of Women in Videogames|url=http://www.thunderboltgames.com/opinion/lara-croft-and-the-future-of-women-in-videogames|publisher=Thunderboltgames.com|accessdate=2013-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023061546/http://www.thunderboltgames.com/opinion/lara-croft-and-the-future-of-women-in-videogames|archive-date=2013-10-23|dead-url=yes}}</ref> 不過、將強勢女性編排為主要角色的做法卻也常受到注重銷售量的人士所懷疑。<ref name="Dring">{{cite web|last=Dring|first=Christopher|title="Women are the future of gaming" - how Tomb Raider and co have put females back on the agenda|url=http://www.mcvuk.com/news/read/women-are-the-future-of-gaming/0111714|publisher=Mcvuk.com|accessdate=2013-10-22|archive-date=2013-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131027055416/http://www.mcvuk.com/news/read/women-are-the-future-of-gaming/0111714|dead-url=no}}</ref>

例如在2012年及2013年的[[E3电子娱乐展|E3]]上<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/wikis/e3/Big_Games_at_E3_2012|title=Big Games at E3 2012 - E3 - Electronics Entertainment Expo Wiki Guide - IGN|publisher=|accessdate=2017-01-20|archive-date=2016-10-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161015163217/http://www.ign.com/wikis/e3/Big_Games_at_E3_2012|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/wikis/e3/Big_Games_at_E3_2013|title=Big Games at E3 2013 - E3 - Electronics Entertainment Expo Wiki Guide - IGN|publisher=|accessdate=2017-01-20|archive-date=2016-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027062141/http://www.ign.com/wikis/e3/Big_Games_at_E3_2013|dead-url=no}}</ref>，[[IGN|IGN]]的數據顯示電子遊戲中的女性主角在2012年至2013年期間成長了4%<ref>Starr, Kyle. "[https://web.archive.org/web/20140410081307/http://thestarrlist.com/2013/08/01/e3-2013-genregender-breakdown E3 2013: Genre/Gender Breakdown]" (via [[Internet_Archive|Internet Archive]]). Thestarrlist.com. 1 August 2013.</ref>。除了越來越多團隊朝著製作有女性角色的遊戲的方向前進，其它形式的努力也已經發生。例如Women in Games International和[[大洛杉磯地區|大洛杉磯地區]]的女童軍合作推出電子遊戲更新檔，以祈女童軍能提升對科學、技術、工程和數學的興趣<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.womeningamesinternational.org/work-learn-play.html|title=Girl Scout Patch|publisher=Womeningamesinternational.org|accessdate=2013-10-22|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131023060739/http://www.womeningamesinternational.org/work-learn-play.html|archivedate=2013-10-23}}</ref>。在[[斯堪地那維亞|斯堪地那維亞]]、有為了使女性參與遊戲而舉辦的[[LAN_party|LAN party]]。<ref name=dillon />

